IBYCUS

and the son of gold-girh Hyllis, aye and he to whom Troilus for loveliness of form was likened forthwith both by Trojan and Danaam e'ven as gold thrice refined might be likened to mountain copper.

Theirs it is to share beauty for ever, and thine, too, Polycrates, shall be a glory, even as my glory

in song, unfading.
